DirectoryListReadCall.description:
Read a list from a directory. If it's called from an EO context the fileName of the associated FileConfig will  be used to filter the result, e.g. *.html. 
Offers also general access methods like read(String filePath, String fileName) for java access.
DirectoryListReadCall.author: Werner Diwischek

DirectoryMapReadCall.description: Read a list from a directory. The file names will replace toReplace (default "_") by replaceBy (default "") and fileEnding(default ".html") will be removed.
DirectoryMapReadCall.author: Werner Diwischek

DirectoryReadCall.description:
Defines a file read operation for a directory configuration @DirectoryConfig 
specified by fileConfigKey defined in @FileReadCall. 
The fileName instance field will be validated against the fileName in the FileConfig as pattern.
DirectoryReadCall.author: Werner Diwischek

DirectoryWriteCall.description: Defines a file write operation for a directory configuration @DirectoryConfig specified by fileConfigKey.
